image_analysis.description: A photograph of a row of six white lockers built into a recessed wall area. The lockers are tall and narrow, each with a silver handle, a circular lock mechanism, and a small circular identification tag at the top. The lockers are set against off-white walls. To the right, an open doorway is visible, showing a door handle and part of another room. The floor in front of the lockers is covered with a dark, textured mat or carpet.
image_analysis.layout: The image shows a centered view of the locker unit, with a wall on the left and a doorway on the right. A watermark/document ID is located in the bottom right corner.

notes: The image is a standard forensic or investigative photograph. There are small labels or numbers on the lockers that are too small to read clearly, though they appear to be standard locker identification tags.
